headline: Uber and its CEO donate $1 million each to Trump's inaugural fund
summary: The ride-hailing firm joins a list of several large businesses that have sought to build a positive relationship with the incoming Trump administration after he won the election in November.  The donations by Uber and Khosrowshahi were first reported by The Wall Street Journal earlier in the day.  OpenAI CEO Sam Altman is planning to make a personal donation of $1 million to the inaugural fund, an OpenAI spokesperson confirmed last week.

summary: Few businesses have disrupted entire industries like Uber Technologies (NYSE: UBER) has done to the taxi market.
